briefdescription.para: A pointer to the QUdpSocket class.

detaileddescription.para: The QUdpSocket class is a subclass of QAbstractSocket that allows the sending and receiving of UDP (User Datagram Protocol) datagrams. Used to bind an adress and port to transfer data.

briefdescription.para: gpiolis1 is a pointer to the GPIOlis function
rftimer is a pointer to the QTimer function
Stores the result of the pow() function in signal processing.
The size of variable storage in data arrays.

detaileddescription.para: Initialises data buffers for incoming EMG data, and generates plot objects to which buffers attach. The constructor also defines a highpass Butterworth filter, creates appropriate files in which to store log data, and initialises the ADC and UDP.
Exits the GPIOlis() object and deletes the GUI window and it's components

briefdescription.para: Performs the data processing and filtering of the input signals.

detaileddescription.para: "hp1" is an instance of a high pass Butterworth IIR filer, of order given by the input parameter. The time-smoothed power of the signal is calculated, added to the plots through the memmove() function, and saved. A 1 channel UDP is sent to test control of the game.

parameterdescription.para: The IIR filter order for processing.

briefdescription.para: Refreshes the GUI window plot every 20ms.
Generates and updates the components of the Pong game's GUI window.

detaileddescription.para: This class instantiates the game components (the GUI scene, paddles, ball and scoreboard), and updates them based on the incoming EMG signal through the Qt signal slot mechanism.
